Counterfeiter Sentenced to Twenty Years Imprisonment 
A counterfeiter in Vietnam has been sentenced to 20 years' imprisonment
for being guilty of circulating 104 million vnd of counterfeit money,
Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported today.
The sentence was made by the people's court of Vietnam's northern
border province of Lang Son.
On June 1st, 1996, Tran Quoc Loi exchanged regular currency with a
Chinese and gave him 104 million vnd in counterfeit money.
The counterfeit, mainly 10,000 and 50,000 notes hidden in sacks of
peanuts, was discovered at Ma Chi border gate and was incinerated after
the trial.
